    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "`-u NONE` skips initialization files and plugins, but still sets up Nvim defaults in `_defaults.lua`. Should defaults be skipped with `-u NONE`?\r\n\r\nIn particular this might make tests (many of which use `-u NONE`) simpler, as they will automatically circumvent `_defaults.lua` (rather than using [other workarounds](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/26437)).",
